interpretations: Swarm has strong lane hygiene: 94.6% lanes close cleanly (MERGED/DONE).
C1 is managed by the 'superseded by' protocol: nodes detect duplicates and explicitly abandon the inferior lane.
C3 risk is very low at small lane counts; may increase at scale as coordinator tracking complexity grows.
Administrative closures inflate ABANDONED count — true duplicate-work C1 is ~30% of abandoned lanes.
